# OK WebStart — Agency Website

> Future-forward web development for ambitious brands.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
TESTE-2.0/
├── assets/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── style.css          # Single shared stylesheet
│   ├── imgs/
│   │   └── LOGO-HEADER.png    # Header logo
│   └── js/
│       └── main.js            # Single shared JavaScript file
├── pages/
│   ├── about.html             # About page
│   ├── contact.html           # Contact page
│   └── services.html          # Services page
├── index.html                 # Homepage (root)
└── README.md                  # This file
```

---

## 🎨 Design System

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| Main | `#010d5b` |
| Accent | `#ffb000` |
| Background | `#030d3e` |
| Success / Green | `#10b981` |
| Text | `#c9d1e9` |
| Text Muted | `#7680a8` |

**Fonts:** Syne (display/headings) + DM Sans (body) — loaded via Google Fonts.

---

## 📦 Dependencies (CDN — no install required)

| Library | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Lenis | `1.0.34` | Smooth scrolling |
| ScrollReveal | `4.0.9` | Scroll entrance animations |
| Google Fonts | — | Syne + DM Sans |

No build tools. No npm. No bundler. Open `index.html` in a browser and it works.

---

## 🚀 How to Run

**Option 1 — Direct open**
Open `index.html` in any modern browser.

**Option 2 — Live Server (recommended)**
If you use VS Code, install the **Live Server** extension, right-click `index.html` and select "Open with Live Server". This gives you hot reload on save.

**Option 3 — Any static host**
Upload the entire `TESTE-2.0/` folder to Netlify, Vercel, or GitHub Pages.

